sentence: Really it is a fine painting app , especially for the price ( free ) .

However I have been looking for an app like the paint app on Microsoft computers, so I could copy images and paste them here or draw straight lines, and this app does not have these features.

sentence: This is a great app .
content: This is a great app. This is basically Photoshop. Now, you may be asking, why am I saying that this is Photoshop? The ability to load photos, layers, a transparent color, the stamp feature, and more, makes this the perfect substitute for Photoshop. I have edited many photos with this. Sure, it may have it's limitations, but it's still great.

sentence: So nearly a great app .
content: So nearly a great app. But saving works badly (you aren't prompted to choose a path), and the function i most need (pixel perfect crop) is impossible to use. It zones out every time you select it... and it's impossibly touchy and keeps committing before you've finished adjusting. I tried about 15 times or more before giving up. Real shame as this is almost, otherwise what all the other apps fall to be. (Simple and powerful)
replyContent: Fixing these issues is planned for the future. Sorry, we are just pro-bono volunteers working in our free time on this free open source non-profit project... any help, e.g., as a developer would be highly appreciated. Thanks!

sentence: The only app I 've actually sought actively to positively review .

So I use a lot of art software on my phone, a ridiculous amount, but this is still my standby and tbh fave. sentence: The best simple paint\drawing app I 've found .
content: The best simple paint\drawing app I've found. It's possible to do some quite complex picture editing with a good range of tools, much more than most simple draw apps offer. Minimal permissions, most importantly no Internet permission and no ads. It would be great to have options when saving. Unfortunately it reduces the resolution and removes the EXIF data (most similar apps do the same), else it would be perfect.
replyContent: Thank you. Fixing these issues is planned for the future. Sorry, we are just pro-bono volunteers working in our free time on this free open source non-profit project... any help, e.g., as a developer would be highly appreciated. Thanks again for your kind understanding!

sentence: I 'm honestly surprised by this app .
content: I'm honestly surprised by this app. It works. You can tell that there is work out into it. That alone isn't special, however it does not have ads, in-app-purchases of any kind or even network access to grab your personal data. I expected I'd have to block network access. But I did not. Good app, worked fine for my purposes so far. Highly recommend. Would consider donating if the option was given.

sentence: Do n't know what has happened .
content:
Don't know what has happened. I've used this app for several years, and 
loved it for it's simplicity, ease of use, user friendliness, and wide 
range of capabilities. For some reason however, I'm now having problems 
with it. Whenever I use the "Fill" function to put a transparent background 
in any sort of project I'm working on, it now force-closes on me. As I 
said, I don't know why it's happening now, because I've performed the exact 
same process countless times. I love this app, and I use the Hell out of 
it, so please fix whatever bug is causing this issue, so I can put my 
rating back up to 5 stars.
replyContent: Please try the new version.

sentence: Has potential , but not there yet .
content:
Has potential, but not there yet. The 'Load image' option down-samples the 
image to a lower resolution and a new image has no option to specify the 
canvas size or output resolution. Needs a dedicated pan and zoom tool to 
save having to use gestures which is difficult when using a phone with one 
hand (including holding it). Colour picker view doesn't accurately reflect 
the chosen colour. Looks washed out. UI design is very nice though. Looks 
modern and easy to use on the whole.

things about this app is how you can zoom in close enough to see every 
pixel in the image which makes it quite handy for precise drawing. Also 
another great addition is how you can draw so easily using the tools this 
app has! This is hands down the best app for pixel art!

sentence: downloaded to make a `` quick '' edit for a meme -- I was n't doing anything too complex but it ended up taking an hour and was frustrating the entire time .
content: downloaded to make a "quick" edit for a meme -- I wasn't doing anything too complex but it ended up taking an hour and was frustrating the entire time. The fact that whenever you undo while zoomed in, it resets the zoom, is infuriating especially as the 'pinch and drag' zoom is finicky. The clone tool, which i was using the most so i could move letters around, is the most functionally useless piece of garbage that I have ever had the displeasure of handling. Whenever you touch it the wrong way it's either reapplying the clone or stamping the wrong thing everywhere (leading to those dreaded undos). Still 2 stars though, because I did end up finishing it the way I wanted and there are literally no other halfway decent photo manipulators on here
replyContent: Please try the new version.

sentence: It 's a good editor and has the potential to be even much , much more !
content: It's a good editor and has the potential to be even much, much more! It can create pics with transparency and is integrated with "Pocket Code" so it's easy to take a created pick, drop it into Pocket code, then pull it back out and modify it, then re-save and repeat until it's perfect. It still needs features like mirror, more shapes like polygons n-point, but it's a very good start and pretty easy to use too! Now it is a little laggy on undoes even on my Samsung Galaxy 5, but with such a dedicated team as Catrobat I'm sure it will really grow in to a truly amazing and professional editor/creator!

Otherwise, this is a wonderful little tool. Thank you for writing it!

sentence: I have taken it upon myself to find an image editor for Android that can do what is a simple task using Windows XP 's MS Paint : Load a large PNG file with no drop in resolution- which your image editor failed to do- , use a paint fill tool that functions like the one in MS Paint- which yours did , shockingly- , and save as a PNG with no drop in quality or resolution- which I have n't tested yet for you due to quality being lost upon loading the image .
content: I have taken it upon myself to find an image editor for Android that can do what is a simple task using Windows XP's MS Paint: Load a large PNG file with no drop in resolution- which your image editor failed to do-, use a paint fill tool that functions like the one in MS Paint- which yours did, shockingly-, and save as a PNG with no drop in quality or resolution- which I haven't tested yet for you due to quality being lost upon loading the image. Your app didn't make the cut... unfortunately none have...
replyContent: Hi, the reason for scaling down was that Pocket Paint was meant to be primarily used together with Pocket Code, and for that it makes sense to scale down large images to the screen size since they are needed only on the screen of the device. We are thinking of having an option that would allow changing this behavior in a future release.
